                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/185: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-20T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 20, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 21—2:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1012. My 1010, November 19, 7 p.m., paragraph 3. Following from American Consul
                    at Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“November 19, 8 p.m. Japanese Consul General at Shanghai has just
                            informed me that he had a conversation today with Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs urging latter to permit Japanese representatives to participate
                            in Provisional Court negotiations but that Wang declined to do so.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
